Description: We created Tabber to let people order and pay in restaurants with their own smartphones.
Headquarters Regions: Greater Miami Area, East Coast, Southern US
Full Description: Have you ever been irritated in a restaurant when you wanted to order and the waiter was not around or just ignored you? Well, many people have that issue every day. Waiting is unacceptable. That is why we created Tabber to let people order and pay in restaurants with their own smartphones. Never try to get the attention of a waiter again, dine at your own pace without interruptions. After one year of development and testing, we were selected by a Miami-based startup accelerator to be in their 2013 class. That was an exciting recognition of our work and we decided to make Miami our home. After that, we refined the technology and the business and geared up for our official launch. In a nutshell, Tabber allows the users to find restaurants, browse their menus, place orders for dine-in or take-out and pay the tab. It cuts all the wait and provides a great experience for the client, while expediting operations for the restaurants and increasing revenue. Here is the kick: it is 100% free for the restaurants. No need for any new equipment or complex implementation, it is a self-service model. This translates into scalability. We will have our commercial launch at the Collision Conference in Las Vegas on May 13th. The US is our current target market, but we designed Tabber to be launched anywhere in the world with little effort.  Everything is in place, all we need now is to get an initial round of seed money to have strong sales and marketing. You can make all the difference right now - join us in making Tabber a huge success!

Description: Clean technology, Research & Development, Innovation, consumer goods
Headquarters Regions: Greater Los Angeles Area, Inland Empire, West Coast
Full Description: We are a team of PhDs with 30+ years of total experience in STEM disciplines including physics, engineering, material science and additive manufacturing. We have a proven track record of peer reviewed publications and patented technologies. In Tech New Logica we believe that even small improvements matter and lead to a better world. Using our extensive knowledge and passion for innovation and green technology we come up with simple yet elegant solutions to existing problems. We aim to transform today’s dreams into reality tomorrow. Because we care about our future generation. We developed GreenSert, the first and the only pocket-size sustainable cup, to eliminate nonrecyclable paper cups which contaminate our environment.  GreenSert is based on our patented technology, the first and the only cup that is compact, nontoxic, easy to clean, and of course, sustainable. The cup consists of a flexible insulating waterproof body made of high quality food grade silicone rubber and comes with an insulating sleeve made from recycled paper, which we call RecyClad. GreenSert is plastic free and nontoxic, super compact, 100% recyclable, microwave and dishwasher safe, hygienic and hypoallergenic with no open pores to harbor bacteria, easy to clean, and weighs 18 g only! RecyClad provides additional thermal insulation and serves as a canvas for custom prints and graphic designs. Both GreenSert & RecyClad can be used together or separately. You can choose to line most 12 oz cups and mugs with GreenSert, while using RecyClad provides extra thermal insulation to protect your hands. Not only you can use GreenSert & RecyClad for your daily coffee needs and get discounts in participating stores for bringing a reusable cup, but you can also take it outdoor as a lightweight and portable cup for your backpacking, hiking, biking, kayaking, and camping adventures!

It is also an escape tool that breaks glass and cuts seatbelts, to save your life in case your car goes underwater. Description: Near Peer Career Learning Videos
Headquarters Regions: Greater New York Area, East Coast, Northeastern US
Full Description: Capture Your Flag is an educational media company and online video content creator that creates knowledge video content to help its audience better plan, pursue and achieve life and career aspirations.  The company is rooted in its Capture Your Flag career documentary interview series which interviews 60 up and coming leaders annually, gathering insight and experience it then shares through its online video website and partner syndication network.  The company also licenses and distributes its career knowledge video to partners across education publishing, e-learning, and multinational media industries.  The Capture Your Flag documentary approach, Near Peer Learning, is designed to fill a gap between peer learning and expert learning.  Interviewees are selected based on a number of criteria, including momentum, sincerity, commitment, and purpose.   Interviews are segmented into individual videos by question and then categorized and curated by aspirational career development theme as well as by industry.  This provides a cross-sectional compare and contrast experience.  Interviews repeat annually, providing a longitudinal experience, inspired by Michael Apted's "Up Series", to learn in real time how experience informs life and career aspiration achievement.  As of February 2013, there are 60 Capture Your Flag interviewees in the documentary series rotation and nearly 2500 videos.  2013 marks Year 4 of the documentary interview series.
